  "texts": [
    "When it imitates humans it tends to drive wages down, and when it complements humans, it tends to drive wages up.",
    "So we should not be making machines that are close images of ourselves, but as different as possible and capable of doing new things.",
    "This change in attitude may have a profound impact on the labor-displacing and labor-augmenting consequences of Gen AI technology, as emphasized by Acemoglu and Restrepo [2], [3], [4].Preparing labor re-skilling, upskilling and retraining programs is crucial to meet the relocation needs triggered by the expected changes in the structure and skill mix of the future workforce, especially in sectors under a direct impact of Gen AI tools and models.As Acemoglu and Johnson [1] concluded based on a thorough review of technology from Neolithic times to the ascent of artificial intelligence, technology is not our destiny.",
    "Even at this age of relentless expansion of generative AI systems, concentration of power and wealth, and seemingly unstoppable descend into technological singularity, their new book \"Power and Progress\" is an essential reminder that we can, and must, take back control and secure the best future for mankind.",
